iconAttributes.iconText: After helping Manchester United to three league titles and two FA Cups, Roy Keane was appointed club captain in 1997 following Eric Cantona’s retirement. In the 1998-99 season, he led his side to a historic treble of the Premier League, FA Cup and Champions League. His performance against Juventus in the semi-final of the Champions League is often regarded as the finest hour in his illustrious footballing career.

Jay-Jay Okocha was at his most prolific in terms of goal scoring at Fenerbahçe, the midfielder falling just short of averaging a goal every two games for the Turkish side in his two seasons at the club. Many of his goals came from free-kicks, his quality at set-pieces making him a threat from anywhere around the penalty area.
